	<string id="ui_mcm_better_stats_bars_use_game_values">
		<text>Use Game Values</text>
	</string>
	<string id="ui_mcm_better_stats_bars_use_game_values_desc">
		<text>Enabling this option will make bars represent protection against actual game threats (npcs, mutants, anomalies), based on their damage values, elemental types. This will also include corrected of outfit and helmet protection behavior. You can choose these options:\n \n
		None: Disables the option.\n
		Max: The bar at maximum represents maximum damage possible to receive. For this case, 1/3rds of the bar usually represents fire, acid, psy fields, weak mutants and pistol caliber firearms.\m
		2/3rds of the bar represents anomaly mines such as electric, gravitational anomalies, burners acid pools, psy dog attacks, average strength mutants and intermediate firearms.\n
		The full bar represents protection against the strongest mines, fields, controller attacks, the strongest mutants and high caliber firearms.\n
		Max (No Mines): Same as Max but anomaly mines are not taken into results. Useful if you want to know exact protection against fields and plan to evade mines rather than knowing how much damage you take from them.</text>

	</string>
